# Beckerman Companion

Household tool for Simon and Chiara. Current scope is travel-day tracking for UK Statutory Residence Test day counts only.

## Source of truth

- Build spec: `start.md`
- Project decisions and ops: `docs/PROJECT.md`
- When present, read `docs/israel_move_source_of_truth.md` and `docs/israel_move_year_one_priorities.md` before large changes.

## Technical constraints

- Supabase for database and hosting; MCP server deploys as a Supabase Edge Function (not Vercel).
- TypeScript throughout; use the official MCP SDK.
- Out of scope unless explicitly requested: advisor memory, vectors, web UI, deeming-day logic, email ingestion. Use TODO comments instead of building.

## Style

- No em dashes in code comments or README.
- Sparse comments; explain why, not what.
- Counting logic for `days_in_country` must stay clear and well tested.

## Simple setup (for humans, not experts)

The AI cannot open your Supabase or GitHub accounts by itself. You run a few commands once on your Mac; after that the AI can help with code in this folder.

**1. GitHub (share and back up the code)**  
Tools: `gh` is installed via Homebrew (`/opt/homebrew/bin/gh`). In Terminal:

1. `gh auth login` and finish the steps in the browser.
2. From this repo folder: `gh repo create beckerman-companion --private --source=. --remote=origin --push`  
   Change the name or use `--public` if you prefer.

**2. Supabase (database and hosting)**  
Tools: `supabase` CLI is installed via Homebrew. In Terminal: `supabase login` and sign in in the browser when asked.

**3. Supabase in Cursor (so the AI can help with your project)**  
This is not installed with Homebrew. In Cursor: **Settings → Tools & MCP → Add MCP server**. Type: **HTTP**. URL: `https://mcp.supabase.com/mcp`. Complete login when Cursor asks. Optional detail: [Supabase MCP docs](https://supabase.com/docs/guides/getting-started/mcp).

**4. Household API tokens (later, for Claude)**  
Simon and Chiara each get a long random secret (not your Supabase password). Store them in a password manager. They go in Supabase Edge Function secrets and in each person’s Claude connector. Full notes live in `docs/PROJECT.md` when you need them.

**5. Country names**  
Use full English names in the database (example: `United Kingdom`). The app may accept short forms like UK or GB and turn them into `United Kingdom`.

When helping the user, prefer short checklists and avoid protocol jargon unless they ask. Point to `start.md` for the product spec and `docs/PROJECT.md` for longer operational detail.
